{"question": "Let $p + q + r = 0$. Evaluate $\left( \frac{p}{q+r} + \frac{q}{r+p} + \frac{r}{p+q} \right) \left( \frac{q+r}{p} + \frac{r+p}{q} + \frac{p+q}{r} \right)$.", "steps": [{"explanation": "Given that p + q + r = 0, we can use this condition to simplify the expression.", "mathematical_explanation": "$p + q + r = 0 \implies q + r = -p$, $r + p = -q$, and $p + q = -r$."}, {"explanation": "Substitute these values into the first part of the given expression.", "mathematical_explanation": "\begin{align*}
\frac{p}{q+r} & = \frac{p}{-p} = -1, \\
\frac{q}{r+p} & = \frac{q}{-q} = -1, \\
\frac{r}{p+q} & = \frac{r}{-r} = -1.
\end{align*}"}, {"explanation": "Therefore, the sum in the first parenthesis simplifies to", "mathematical_explanation": "-1 - 1 - 1 = -3"}, {"explanation": "For the second part, substitute similarly.", "mathematical_explanation": "\begin{align*}
\frac{q+r}{p} & = \frac{-p}{p} = -1, \\
\frac{r+p}{q} & = \frac{-q}{q} = -1, \\
\frac{p+q}{r} & = \frac{-r}{r} = -1.
\end{align*}"}, {"explanation": "Thus, the sum in the second parenthesis also equals", "mathematical_explanation": "-1 - 1 - 1 = -3"}, {"explanation": "Multiplying both simplified parts together gives us the final answer.", "mathematical_explanation": "(-3)(-3) = 9"}], "final_answer": "9", "answers": [{"answers": "9", "isCorrect": true}, {"answers": "-9", "isCorrect": false}, {"answers": "6", "isCorrect": false}, {"answers": "3", "isCorrect": false}], "hint": "Use the condition p + q + r = 0 to simplify each fraction in the expression.", "keywords": ["mathematics", "equation", "simplification", "expression"]}

